The jhanas are a series of highly pleasurable altered states of They appear in both Buddhism and Hinduism (under different spelling), and appear similar to states described in other mystical traditions, including Christianity, Mormonism, and Depending on the context, they’re used for different purposes, ranging from a direct route Enlightenment to a warmup exercise for other Newcomers to jhanas also frequently use it as a launchpad to explore other contemplative and ethical Why would I want to learn the jhanas? The jhanas are profoundly blissful and can have cascading positive effects, like a “mentality of abundance,” and make it easier to engage in Practitioners often use hyperbolic terms, such as “life-changing,” “better than sex,” and “they completely absolved me of the notion that happiness comes from outside ” Preliminary brain images support these descriptions, suggesting jhana meditators have learned to turn on the pleasure centers in their brain without external One of our favorite jhana practitioner quotes is “Why would I have a second piece of chocolate cake when I know I can beat that by in minutes with my eyes closed?” Learning the jhanas also looks excitingly tractable — for a long time jhana practice was thought to be limited to monastics, but in the last years jhana practice has been rapidly New evidence and schools of thought suggest anyone can learn these Are you injecting energy into the brain? Neurofeedback is an effective, , safe, , and intervention regularly used by clinical psychologists and in consumer We are not inducing states via something like current or We monitor brainwaves and then give audio, visual, or haptic feedback to let the user know they’re on the right This serves like a map in unfamiliar territory, but you do the walking and develop the relevant muscles How does neurofeedback help? In some ways it’s easier to imitate Lebron James than it is the Dalai Because meditation is invisible and preverbal, words are a limited tool for describing our inner experiences, and learning to meditate involves lots of guesswork and imprecise Individualized and realtime feedback based on brainwaves can give faster and more precise feedback, improving motivation and If you have direct access to pleasure, could you become addicted? Jhana meditators show no sign of On the contrary, practitioners often report positive changes in other cravings and Some Buddhist meditation circles use the term “jhana junkie,” but in a very specific In these circles, the jhanas are used as warmup exercises for practices that lead to desirable, “Insights.” The term “jhana junkie” refers to someone that only practices the jhana and never moves One teacher likes to say “it’s very easy to cure a ‘jhana junkie,’ you just have to show them the value of ” Since good meditation requires hard work, isn t this scheme doomed to fail? We don’t want to swap what the Buddhist’s call “right effort” for instant But “hard work” can also mask poor pedagogy and stagnant Access to the jhanas can have profound mental health benefits, increase motivation and ability for other forms of contemplative practice, and cascade into relationships and We believe in helping people access these states in ways that are accessible, safe, and Will focusing on specific states increase striving, which is what meditation is designed to prevent? There’s a paradox in meditation between the method, which hinges upon “letting go” and the objective, which rests on a clear In the same way that teachers correct practice via instruction, we hope our feedback will help users learn how to navigate this paradox more effectively, not Does the use of technology taint or nullify the spiritual benefit of jhana practice? At one point singing bowls were cutting edge Meditation teachers have been providing neurofeedback for millennia, and many more technologies and techniques from retreats to chanting have carried the jhanas through time and EEG and ML algorithms are new tools of our age, and we hope will be equally treasured contributions to jhana practice in the Are you divorcing jhanas from their ethical context, and risking morality in the process? SIGN IN Log in Cart Item added to your cart Check out Continue shopping Frequently Asked Questions If you have a question that isn t answered here, please email us . Auctions How do I bid? There are 2 ways to bid: "normal" and "proxy" bidding To place a normal bid: enter your bid above the current bid, by the minimum increment (1,000 sats) To place a proxy bid: enter the maximum amount you will pay When you place a normal bid, you will likely be immediately outbid if there is an open proxy When you place a proxy bid, you ll see bids placed automatically (up to your limit) as the auction moves How can I tell if I m the current bidder? You will see (You) listed next to the current Who is "Anon" ? All bids are anonymous on Rigly, so all bids (other than yours) will say Bitcoin mining Why should I buy mining hashrate? Rigly mining plans allow you to start mining bitcoin without buying an expensive ASIC mining Auctions offer a new way to obtain hashrate at a fair market You can apply your hashrate to support the network via pooled or solo Mining enables you to earn bitcoin right from the protocol and potentially earn a profit, depending on future mining difficulty and market ^ The above is not investment How do I monitor my mining? You can monitor your mining at your mining You will receive email status updates from Rigly when your mining begins and Which mining pools are supported by Rigly? All bitcoin mining pools are supported by We suggest you use a PPS or FPPS pools for consistent Many Rigly users use Braiins pool or Luxor How often will I see bitcoin earned from my mining? Payout times will vary by mining See your pool for Many pools offer a minimum payout amount of Do you offer mining auctions for other coins besides bitcoin? Rigly is bitcoin Is bitcoin mining hashrate a security? The output of mining rigs (hashrate) is not a Rigly s mining subscriptions are tied to ASIC mining rigs listed by mining farms around the These rigs produce hashes per your configuration and you are in control of how your hashrate is Will I earn a profit from my mining? Your mining profitability depends upon a number of factors: future mining difficulty, hashprice, transaction fees and Mining profits will vary based on pool payout Mining Plans Is electricity cost included in the price? Your mining hashrate price includes all electricity and hosting facility Why would someone rent out their bitcoin rigs? Isn t bitcoin mining profitable? No one knows where mining difficulty and hashprice will be in the Rigly offers a way for bitcoin miners to potentially earn more from their hashrate, over the long term, than they would by mining What fees does Rigly charge? Our auction platform fee is 3% and is paid by the The fee is paid via During your mining term, you will see a periodic drop in received hashrate when the fee is Are mining plans paid in USD or BTC? All payments are in bitcoin (BTC) based on the transaction price in Payment and deposits What happens if my mining rig goes offline? If your plan s ASIC mining rigs fail to perform within the Service Level Agreement or go offline for an extended period of time, you receive an extension or a refund based on the percentage What if I change my mind? Can I get a refund? If your mining experiences an outage, is below the speed average day, or otherwise fails to deliver, you will receive a refund based on the TH s you should have However, Rigly is not able to refund if you change your mind or otherwise want to cancel your Is this cloud mining?
